onfirmed by an elevated methemoglobin level of at least 10%.  If patient does not respond to administration of oxygen, clinically significant methemoglobinemia should be treated with methylene blue 1 to 2 mg/kg by slow intravenous injection over 5 minutes.', 'Synergism', 'Sodium nitrite should be used with caution in the presence of other methemoglobin-inducing drugs.', 'Major', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/293616/', '', 'Hydroxocobalamin, Fomepizole, Ipecac, Dexrazoxane, Oxygen, Lanthanum carbonate, Difelikefalin, Cobicistat, Deferoxamine, Levoleucovorin, Promethazine, More', 'Ropivacaine, Levobupivacaine, Bupivacaine, Mepivacaine, Meloxicam, Etidocaine', 1767369485);
